definitions.definition: To form into a whole by uniting its parts; to construct; to build.
examples: to fabricate a bridge or ship

definitions.definition: To form by art and labor; to manufacture; to produce.
To invent and form; to forge; to devise falsely.
examples: to fabricate a lie or story

definitions.definition: To cut up an animal as preparation for cooking, particularly used in reference to fowl.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To form into a whole by uniting its parts; to construct; to build.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To form by art and labor; to manufacture; to produce.
( transitive ) To invent and form; to forge; to devise falsely.
( transitive , cooking ) To cut up an animal as preparation for cooking, particularly used in reference to fowl.
